snippet.textDisplay: Engineering advice : on a rigid shaft on bearings, there should be only 2 bearings and no more.  In industrial heavy-duty application a shaft with 3 or 4 bearings would get bearings blown up quite quickly.  Here hou could without any problem spare 2 out of 4 bearings on each screw ;-)
